Write a program to find the factorial of a given number. The factorial of a number n is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to n.

It is denoted by n! and defined as:

n! = n × (n−1) × (n−2) × ... × 1

For example, 5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1 = 120

Input Format

A single integer n representing the number.

Constraints

0 <= n <= 12

Output Format

Print the factorial of the given number.

Sample Input 0

5
Sample Output 0

120

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {

    int n,ans = 1;
    scanf("%d",&n);
    int a=n;
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        ans=ans*a;
        a-=1;
    }   
    printf("%d",ans);
    return 0;
}


